					<section>
            <h2>Nebulae</h2>
	          <p style="font-size:.7em;">"Nebula" is Latin for “cloud”. These are more varied than any other type of object. Some are star-forming regions, others are left behind when a star no longer exists.</p>
						<div style="margin:0 auto;text-align:left;max-width:75%;">
							<p style="font-size:.6em;"><u>Reflection nebulae</u> glow from light bouncing off of the dust between stars.</p>
							<p style="font-size:.6em;"><u>Emission nebulae</u> emit light from the gases in them.</p>
							<p style="font-size:.6em;"><u>Dark (absorption) nebulae</u> block the light of stars behind them and appear as a “hole” in space.</p>
						</div>
