					<section>
            <h2>Galaxies</h2>
            <p style="font-size:.7em;">Large collections of stars, gas and dust far outside our galaxy.<br />There is estimated to be 100 billion galaxies of many types.</p>
						<div style="margin:0 auto;text-align:left;max-width:75%;">
							<p style="font-size:.6em;"><u>Spiral galaxies</u> are similar to our own. </p>
							<p style="font-size:.6em;"><u>Elliptical galaxies</u> tend to have little gas and dust to form new stars.</p>
							<p style="font-size:.6em;"><u>Dwarf galaxies</u> are mostly gas and dust in a poorly organized structure.</p>
							<p style="font-size:.6em;"><u>Irregular galaxies</u> (everything else).</p>
						</div>
